/-
ProgressCensus.lean — the sorry/dependency census for the FLT progress
tooling. Since 2026-07-23 (Deyao's final design) this file is held OPEN
in the resident report server — `lake serve` on FIFOs under
`.report-server/`, run as the systemd user unit
`flt-report-server.service` (the sole lifecycle mechanism) — and
progress-tree.py's run_census() handshakes the fresh session when
needed and refreshes this file per query (didChange, or
didClose+didOpen when sources changed); elaboration emits the census as
ONE JSON object through the `#eval` info diagnostic. The same file also
runs standalone as `lake lean ProgressCensus.lean` (lake builds the
import closure incrementally, the JSON lands on stdout) — a manual
debugging entry, not part of any automatic route.

The import block between the BEGIN/END markers below — including the
baked-in input path and the census-input fingerprint line (which makes
a names/root input change visible as a BODY text change, so the report
server re-elaborates without an import reload) — is GENERATED by
progress-tree.py on every run, from a scan of the Fermat/ source tree
EXCLUDING the root aggregator `Fermat` (whose `#assert_no_sorry` gate
fails by design mid-project). Do not edit the block by hand. The body
after the END marker is hand-maintained.

Input (progress-census-input.json, written by progress-tree.py):
  {"names": ["<tracked decl>", ...], "root": "fermat_last_theorem"}
Output (one compressed JSON object on stdout):
  {"entries": [{"name", "missing"} | {"name", "missing", "own",
               "clean", "kids"}],
   "sorried": [{"name", "module"}],
   "root": {"missing": true} | {"missing", "coneSorry", "badAxioms"}}

This file lives at the repo root, OUTSIDE the `Fermat` lib glob
(lakefile: `lean_lib Fermat`), so `lake build` never picks it up.
-/
